@startuml tmu_dkey_to_paak_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title TMU + DKEY To PAAK State Signal Flow\n(DKEY auth + TMU proximity + vehicle state -> Phone-as-Key publication)

participant "DKEY\nDKeyState / AuthMode" as DKEY #E8F7E8
participant "TMU\nSignalBars / service mode" as TMU #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState" as Veh #F4F7FB
participant "PAK\nphone-as-key owner" as PAK #FFF4CC
participant "Access observers /\nconsumer ECUs" as Obs #FCE8FF

== PAAK Inputs ==

DKEY -> PAK : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nDKeyState / AuthMode
TMU -> PAK : frmTmuServiceStateMsg\nSignalBars
Veh -> PAK : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState
activate PAK
PAK -> PAK : normalize stale DKEY / TMU / vehicle inputs
PAK -> PAK : derive PaakState / AuthLevel
PAK -> PAK : derive ProximityState / SyncLatency
note right of PAK
Representative outputs
- PaakState
- AuthLevel
- ProximityState
- SyncLatency
end note

== PAAK Publish ==

PAK -> Obs : frmPhoneAsKeyStateMsg
PAK -> Obs : traceable phone-key state for\naccess consumers and tests
deactivate PAK

note over DKEY, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. DKEY provides digital-key state and auth level
2. TMU provides signal-bar proximity context
3. PAK combines those with drive state
4. PAK publishes consolidated phone-as-key state
end note

@enduml
